  "text": "There are a number of technologies available for the manufacture of microfluidic devices [CITATION_1] . One of the most popular is soft lithography, in which an embossed master mold is generated through photolithography, which is then used to imprint a polymer, polydimethylsiloxane (PDMS). PDMS is optically transparent to wavelengths as short as ~300 nm light, which allows for visible light microscopy, and is also gas permeable allowing for cell respiration. For a thorough review of applications of this fabrication technique in biology, see [CITATION_2] .",
